A 27-year-old, right-handed Caucasian male with 13-year history of UC with primary sclerosing cholangitis presented to the ER with acute onset of left sided headache, left eye proptosis, erythema, and painful eye movements without any visual changes. He reported a recent trip to Spain and denied trauma, sick contacts, urinary symptoms, fever, weight loss, sexually transmitted diseases, or similar illness in family and friends.